Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Lax\[Dash]Foldy Voxelized Sphere vs Exact Mie Scattering", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00001-0001-0001-0001-000000000001"],

Cell["T. M. Nestor \[Dash] Research School of Earth Sciences, ANU", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00001-0001-0001-0001-000000000002"],

Cell["\<\
Discretizes a sphere into space-filling cubes (voxels), assigns each cube a \
Rayleigh T-matrix with cubic Eshelby correction (the depolarization tensor \
for a cube has cubic symmetry with three independent constants A, B, C, where \
C \[NotEqual] 0 unlike a sphere), solves the Lax\[Dash]Foldy self-consistent \
9N\[Times]9N linear system (3 displacement + 6 Voigt strain per cube), and \
compares the total scattered P-wave field with the exact elastic Mie solution.

Units: km/s (velocities), g/cm\\[ThreeSuperior] (densities), km (lengths)
Coordinates: z (axis 0, down), x (axis 1, across), y (axis 2, out of plane)

References:
  Pao & Mow (1973) \[Dash] Diffraction of Elastic Waves
  Korneev & Johnson (1993) \[Dash] Scattering of elastic waves by a sphere
  Shekhar et al. (2023) \[Dash] Lippmann\[Dash]Schwinger T-matrix
  Eshelby (1957) \[Dash] Elastic field of an ellipsoidal inclusion\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00001-0001-0001-0001-000000000003"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1. Bessel/Hankel Functions and Mie Machinery", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00002-0001-0001-0001-000000000001"],

Cell["\<\
Spherical Bessel/Hankel functions and their derivatives, P/S-wave radial \
field coefficients, and the 4\[Times]4 P-SV boundary condition system for \
elastic Mie scattering.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00002-0001-0001-0001-000000000002"],

