Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["13. Five-Channel Extension: SV and SH Incidence", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00015-0001-0001-0001-000000000001"],

Cell["\<\
Extend the P-wave-only comparison to all 5 non-zero scattering channels:\
  P\[Rule]P, P\[Rule]SV, SV\[Rule]P, SV\[Rule]SV, SH\[Rule]SH.

This loads FiveChannelExtension.wl which:
1. Adds SV-incident and SH Mie solves (same 4\[Times]4 matrix, new RHS + 2\[Times]2 SH)
2. Solves Lax\[Dash]Foldy for SV and SH incidence (reusing the system matrix)
3. Computes far-field amplitudes via cubeFarFieldP/S for all 5 channels
4. Generates Re/Im comparison plots

Prerequisites: Evaluate sections 1\[Dash]8 first.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00015-0001-0001-0001-000000000002"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(*", " ",
   RowBox[{"Load", " ", "the", " ", "five", "-",
    RowBox[{"channel", " ", "extension"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n",
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"SetDirectory", "[",
     RowBox[{"NotebookDirectory", "[", "]"}], "]"}], ";"}], "\n",
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Get", "[", "\"\<CubeAnalytic.wl\>\"", "]"}], ";"}], "\n",
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Get", "[", "\"\<FiveChannelExtension.wl\>\"", "]"}],
    ";"}]}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00015-0001-0001-0001-000000000003"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["14. Summary", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00014-0001-0001-0001-000000000001"],

Cell["\<\
The Lax\[Dash]Foldy multiple scattering solution from N voxel scatterers \
converges to the exact Mie solution as the voxel size d \[Rule] 0 (N \[Rule] \
\[Infinity]).

Key observations:
\[Bullet] The full 9\[Times]9 T-matrix (density + stiffness with cubic \
Eshelby correction) captures all three lowest Mie orders: monopole (n=0, bulk \
modulus), dipole (n=1, density), and quadrupole (n=2, shear modulus).
\[Bullet] Each cube has cubic shape anisotropy: the Eshelby depolarization \
tensor has three independent constants (A, B, C) with C \[NotEqual] 0, \
producing four amplification factors and a cubic 6\[Times]6 Voigt stiffness \
where C11\[Dash]C12 \[NotEqual] 2 C44 (Zener ratio \[NotEqual] 1).
\[Bullet] The 9N\[Times]9N Lax\[Dash]Foldy system propagates both \
displacement and strain self-consistently between cubes via the full \
elastodynamic Green\[CloseCurlyQuote]s tensor and its first and second \
spatial derivatives.
\[Bullet] Convergence to the exact Mie solution improves as d/a \[Rule] 0 \
(more cubes per diameter), with the stiffness terms essential for the \
monopole and quadrupole.
\[Bullet] The five-channel extension (section 13) validates all non-zero \
scattering channels: P\[Rule]P, P\[Rule]SV, SV\[Rule]P, SV\[Rule]SV, and \
SH\[Rule]SH, using SV/SH incident states with the same system matrix.

Coordinate system: z (down) = propagation direction, x (across), y (out of \
plane). All velocities in km/s, densities in g/cm\\[ThreeSuperior].\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a1b00014-0001-0001-0001-000000000002"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
